Base tuning target: turret_damage ~ 33% of player base bullet damage, fire_interval ~0.9s, range ~80% of player range.
Cap rule: at 5 turrets, further turret props should convert to quality upgrades (damage/range) instead of count.

;4.5 Stationary Turret     ==========================================================================
Similar to Auto Turret, just cannot move.

Rarity: 1
Base Price: $14
Max Level: 99 (copy-style stacking)
Per purchase: +1 stationary turret spawn each level at valid clear tile.
Suggested tuning: same bullet damage as auto turret, +15% range, -10% fire interval to reward setup play.

'5. Crit, Element, and Synergy Props'

These give crit & status builds more identity, especially since you already have crit chance.

5.1. Razor Focus
Effect: +Crit chance, but -Fire rate.
Synergy:
Works on builds that already stacked firerate from level-ups.
High synergy with crit damage multiplier if you add that stat later.

Rarity: 2
Base Price: $18
Max Level: 3
Level 1: +8% crit chance, -6% fire rate
Level 2: +13% crit chance, -10% fire rate
Level 3: +20% crit chance, -15% fire rate

5.2. Explosive Crits
Effect: Critical hits cause a small explosion around the target, dealing splash damage.
Synergy:
Ties together crit + crowd control.
Combos insanely with ricochet / pierce / shrapnel.

Rarity: 3
Base Price: $24
Max Level: 3
Level 1: crit_explosion_damage = 30% bullet_base, radius = 0.60 tiles
Level 2: crit_explosion_damage = 42% bullet_base, radius = 0.75 tiles
Level 3: crit_explosion_damage = 55% bullet_base, radius = 0.90 tiles
Boss rule: crit explosion damage is reduced by 35% against bosses.

5.3. Frost Brand
Effect: Hits have a small chance to chill enemies, slowing them briefly. If you hit a chilled enemy again, extra damage.
Synergy:
Strong with high firerate (you can proc chill frequently).
Gives non-speed builds some safety through slows.

Rarity: 2
Base Price: $16
Max Level: 3
Level 1: chill_chance = 14%, chill_slow = 20%, chill_duration = 1.2s, re-hit_bonus = +12%
Level 2: chill_chance = 20%, chill_slow = 24%, chill_duration = 1.5s, re-hit_bonus = +18%
Level 3: chill_chance = 28%, chill_slow = 30%, chill_duration = 1.8s, re-hit_bonus = +26%
Boss rule: slow effect is 50% effective on bosses.

5.4. Shock Relay
Effect: Every few hits, chain lightning to nearby enemies for bonus damage (interval scales by level).
Synergy:
Rewards sustained fire (auto-fire weapons).
Great vs clustered waves, weaker vs single boss, so still somewhat balanced.

Rarity: 2
Base Price: $19
Max Level: 3
Level 1: every 8th hit chains to up to 2 enemies, chain_damage = 30% bullet_base
Level 2: every 6th hit chains to up to 3 enemies, chain_damage = 40% bullet_base
Level 3: every 5th hit chains to up to 4 enemies, chain_damage = 50% bullet_base
Chain range: 1.8 / 2.2 / 2.6 tiles by level.

'6.Core Paint System '
Tiles can hold temporary “paint” that affects movement and combat. A tile’s paint has:
Owner state: Neutral / Player Paint / Enemy Paint (enemy paint optional for later).
Intensity: 0-1 , starts high when applied, then decays over time. Effects scale with intensity (fresh paint is stronger, faded paint is weaker).
Sources of paint include:
Player movement (trails / footsteps).
Some attacks (projectiles, explosions, AoE splashes).
Boss skills (enemy ink zones).
Props that convert shield, HP, or kills into paint.
Basic rules for Player Paint (future-proof):
While standing on Player Paint:
Small move-speed bonus (respect existing speed cap).
Small attack / damage bonus vs enemies also standing on your paint.
Optional: tiny HP / shield regen and faster “special/ult” meter gain.
Enemy Paint (for later):
Slows the player, may apply chip damage or debuffs (fog, blind, crit reduction), encouraging the player to “reclaim” the ground with their own paint.
Paint always fades over time, keeping the battlefield dynamic instead of permanently covered.
All paint can be covered by other paint, and the new paint will replace the old paint.

6.1. Curing Paint
Path: Core Paint System (OFF - offensive utility)
Rarity: 2 (Common / Uncommon)
Base Price: $12
Max Level: 3
Core Effect
Your movement leaves a short trail of Player Paint (“curing ink”) on the ground.

Detailed tuning:
Tick interval: 0.5s
Level 1: damage_per_tick = 0.04 * bullet_base, lifetime = 2.0s, radius = 0.69 tiles
Level 2: damage_per_tick = 0.06 * bullet_base, lifetime = 3.0s, radius = 0.78 tiles
Level 3: damage_per_tick = 0.08 * bullet_base, lifetime = 4.0s, radius = 0.90 tiles
Boss rule: paint DoT deals 70% damage to bosses.
Spawn cadence: leave footprint every 0.25s while moving.
Ownership rule: only latest paint owner controls tile effects.

'7. “Set / Combo” Ideas'

7.1. Ballistic Engine (2/3 piece set)
Pieces:
Piercing Rounds + Ricochet Scope (+ Shrapnel Shells as 3rd piece)
Set Bonus:
2-piece: +15% projectile speed, +10% shrapnel proc chance.
3-piece: first ricochet each shot has +20% crit chance.

7.2. Fortress Loop (2/3 piece set)
Pieces:
Carapace + Bone Plating (+ Aegis Pulse as 3rd piece)
Set Bonus:
2-piece: after losing shield, gain 10% move speed for 1.5s.
3-piece: Aegis Pulse emits one extra mini-wave at 40% damage.

7.3. Predator Economy (2/3 piece set)
Pieces:
Wanted Poster + Bandit Radar (+ Lockbox as 3rd piece)
Set Bonus:
2-piece: first bandit kill bounty +30%.
3-piece: bandits drop 1 extra guaranteed coin bundle.

7.4. Cold Circuit (2/3 piece set)
Pieces:
Frost Brand + Shock Relay (+ D.O.T. Rounds as 3rd piece)
Set Bonus:
2-piece: chilled targets take +12% chain lightning damage.
3-piece: shock chains apply mini-chill (10% slow for 0.8s).

Set system rules:
Set bonuses should be additive utility spikes, not run-defining raw multipliers.
A full 3-piece set should add about +12% to +20% effective run power, not more.
Always show active set count in pause/build summary (example: Fortress Loop 2/3).
